{
  "text": "Specifically, in contrast to traditional PC users, mobile users have predictable service demands subject to their locations [CITATION_1] . For example, a mobile user in a shopping center tends to be interested in the local sales, open hour, restaurants and events inside the attended shopping center; such information become useless once he/she leaves the shopping center. In another example, a visitor to a new city would seek for the information on the places of interest, news and weather conditions of that city, while unlikely to be interested in such information of other places.",
